[2] India (Karnataka State)
Date: Sat 18 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Star of Mysore [edited]
<http://www.starofmysore.com/main.asp?type=news&item=8774>

Typhoid claims 1st victim
-------------------------
The deadly disease typhoid, which broke out in
the city during the beginning of February 2006,
has claimed its 1st victim.
A 19-year-old woman was suffering from the
symptoms of the epidemic for the last week and
was taking treatment at home, but when her
condition became serious with high fever, she was
admitted to Vikram Hospital. She died on Thu 16
Feb 2006.
The epidemic was detected on 13 Feb 2006, when
the Corporation Health Officials found out that
the water pipe in the Under Ground Drainage (UGD)
route on Manandavadi Road was getting mixed up
with the drainage water from a pipe which runs
parallel to it. The Corporation had taken up a
survey to locate places where water pipes and UGD
lines pass side by side.
After the epidemic spread to other parts in the
city, district Health officials collected the
blood samples of patients, and typhoid was
confirmed. The District Health and Family Welfare
Officer Dr. Krishnaswamy said that the water
samples from the affected areas were tested for
bacteriological contamination. It was confirmed
that the water was not fit for human consumption.
He regretted that, even after sending daily
reports of water contamination to the City
Corporation, immediate steps have not been taken.
