[3] South Africa (Limpopo Province)
Date: Sun 12 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Zoutnet.co.za [edited]
<http://www.zoutnet.co.za/news/details.asp?StoNum=3971>

Residents told not to panic over typhoid fever outbreak
-------------------------------------------------------
Mr. Phuti Seloba, provincial spokesperson for the
Department of Health and Social Development, said
on Wed 8 Feb 2006 that residents need not panic
with regard to an outbreak of typhoid fever.
Following up on a tip from a member of the public
to investigate a confirmed case of typhoid fever
at the Louis Trichardt Memorial Hospital, the
Zoutpansberger's investigation revealed 12
confirmed cases of typhoid fever in and around
town over a period of 3 weeks. 4 of the patients
who tested positive for the disease live in town,
while the other patients are from Sinthumule,
Tshikwarani, Indermark, Madombidzha, Magau and
Munzhedzi. A couple of months ago, an outbreak of
this deadly disease caused several deaths at
Delmas in Mpumalanga.
[Byline: Andries van Zyl]
